OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Dowries have been illegal in India     
OL,6, since 1961, but the bride's family is  
OL,7, still expected to gift cash, clothes   
OL,8, and jewellery to the groom's family.   
OL,10,FNow, a 27-year-old teacher in the      
OL,11,Fcentral city of Bhopal has started a   
OL,12,Fpetition asking the police to deploy   
OL,13,Fofficers at marriage venues and conduct
OL,14,Fraids to put an end to this "social    
OL,15,Fevil".                                 
OL,17,FGunjan Tiwari (not her real name) tells
OL,18,Fthe BBC her petition is rooted in her  
OL,19,Fown experiences of being rejected by   
OL,20,Fdozens of men over dowry.              
